1
00:01:25,539 --> 00:01:29,890
[Coroner's Diary]

2
00:01:30,670 --> 00:01:33,950
[Episode 26]

3
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:40,509
I think

4
00:01:41,509 --> 00:01:43,590
Li Muyun may have figured out who I am.

5
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:47,310
There's a tactic in warfare called
"startling the snake by striking the grass."

6
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:48,910
He has never seen you before.

7
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:51,039
Even if he grew suspicious
during the autopsy,

8
00:01:51,039 --> 00:01:52,350
he has no proof.

9
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,250
But if you really react,

10
00:01:54,509 --> 00:01:55,970
you'll fall into his trap.

11
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:58,530
I nearly ruined everything
over something so small.

12
00:01:58,530 --> 00:02:00,090
I still lack patience.

13
00:02:02,530 --> 00:02:04,260
You've done very well already.

14
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,530
If it were me,

15
00:02:06,140 --> 00:02:09,199
I might've killed him
on impulse and caused a disaster.

16
00:02:09,530 --> 00:02:10,740
You wouldn't.

17
00:02:11,460 --> 00:02:13,690
You're the most cautious person I know.

18
00:02:14,090 --> 00:02:16,750
You never do anything
you're not certain about.

19
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:19,340
But since returning to the capital,

20
00:02:19,690 --> 00:02:21,950
I'm facing more and more uncertainties.

21
00:02:22,530 --> 00:02:23,860
Because of your father?

22
00:02:27,570 --> 00:02:28,770
He won't listen to me.

23
00:02:29,460 --> 00:02:30,590
How can I be certain?

24
00:02:33,180 --> 00:02:34,060
What worries me now

25
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:35,990
is Prince Jin and Lord Shen's case.

26
00:02:36,570 --> 00:02:38,310
I went to the Ministry of Justice
to find the files,

27
00:02:38,310 --> 00:02:39,910
but they've all been sealed.

28
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:41,579
It seems this matter

29
00:02:41,810 --> 00:02:44,140
is far more complicated than we imagined.

30
00:02:44,410 --> 00:02:45,180
Today, when I saw

31
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:47,250
Li Muyun mention my father,

32
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:51,090
he showed no guilt at all.

33
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:53,340
I thought he was shameless,

34
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,530
and I was furious.

35
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:56,820
But now that I think about it,

36
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:58,970
what if he really has nothing
to be ashamed of?

37
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:01,320
What if he really just did
what he was supposed to do?

38
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,450
What if my father...

39
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:06,530
really did help Prince Jin...

40
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:10,570
Wan,

41
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:12,900
stop overthinking it.

42
00:03:14,850 --> 00:03:16,050
We've just returned.

43
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:20,370
We need to establish ourselves
in the Ministry of Justice before we can act.

44
00:03:20,370 --> 00:03:21,130
Trust me—

45
00:03:22,530 --> 00:03:24,780
the truth will come out sooner or later.

46
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:26,940
We'll uncover it,

47
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:28,410
step

48
00:03:28,810 --> 00:03:29,810
by step.

49
00:03:32,460 --> 00:03:34,690
Prince Sui can speak now.

50
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:37,310
Once his mind is more settled,

51
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,130
I'll ask if he

52
00:03:39,130 --> 00:03:41,329
remembers anything about Consort Jin.

53
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:42,500
Alright.

54
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:45,950
Don't think about these things anymore.

55
00:03:46,090 --> 00:03:49,220
You've worked hard these days.
You should get some rest.

56
00:03:49,340 --> 00:03:51,060
The Ministry of Justice prison

57
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:53,990
isn't exactly a comfortable place
for questioning.

58
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,970
Come on, Your Highness!

59
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:09,620
Come on! Where are you?

60
00:04:09,620 --> 00:04:10,740
The show is going to begin!

61
00:04:10,740 --> 00:04:11,740
Over here!

62
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:13,850
Over here?

63
00:04:14,180 --> 00:04:15,020
I got you!

64
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:16,060
I'm too tired to play.

65
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,300
You guys catch me now.

66
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:19,180
Coming, Sir.

67
00:04:20,829 --> 00:04:22,270
It feels good.

68
00:04:22,450 --> 00:04:24,210
Give my shoulders a massage.

69
00:04:31,060 --> 00:04:32,140
What's going on?

70
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:34,030
Weren't you supposed to catch me?

71
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,830
What are you doing here?

72
00:04:41,570 --> 00:04:42,659
Why are you crying?

73
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:45,080
Which bastard bullied you?

74
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:47,020
I'll take him down right now!

75
00:04:51,770 --> 00:04:55,060
It was you, you bastard!

76
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:59,880
I thought you were dead.

77
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:03,800
How could I be dead?

78
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:04,920
The other day,

79
00:05:05,450 --> 00:05:07,880
someone was killed at Fengqi House.

80
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:10,690
It was a brutal death!

81
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,540
So,

82
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,040
you thought it was me?

83
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:19,670
I've been looking everywhere for you.

84
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:22,670
I went to Fengqi House
and Prince Yi's Mansion

85
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:25,250
but couldn't find you.

86
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:28,060
I heard Chi was investigating the case,

87
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:30,400
so I rushed over.

88
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:31,860
It turned out

89
00:05:32,690 --> 00:05:35,090
Little Wan'er was performing the autopsy.

90
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:38,430
The body really looked a lot like you.

91
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:41,620
It really looked like you.

92
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,540
Even if it wasn't you,

93
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:44,330
the officer said

94
00:05:44,330 --> 00:05:46,659
the deceased spent every day in brothels.

95
00:05:46,659 --> 00:05:47,890
What if...

96
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:50,450
the next one is you?

97
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:54,620
What if you really died?

98
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,740
What am I supposed to do?

99
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:05,810
If I really die,

100
00:06:07,210 --> 00:06:08,420
I'll make sure you

101
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:12,000
stand at the front
of my funeral procession.

102
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:16,300
Fine.

103
00:06:16,940 --> 00:06:18,770
I won't just stand at the front—

104
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:20,890
I'll perform the rites for you,

105
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:21,620
alright?

106
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:30,680
♪ In the long journey of life ♪

107
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:35,409
♪ The meaning of encounters
can never be defined ♪

108
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:43,290
♪ The story isn’t over yet,
and tears are not the only part of it ♪

109
